<p><b>How to fix system common problems?</b> Run a system update to ensure all system components are up to date. Try uninstalling and then reinstalling the software. Check for software conflicts - sometimes two programs can interfere with each other. If the problem is widespread, consider a system restore or resetting your operating system.</p>
<p><b>How to troubleshoot software issues?</b> To do this, you can check error messages and codes, run a system or malware scan, use the task manager or resource monitor to check CPU, memory, disk, and network usage of programs and processes, and search online for similar problems and solutions.</p>
<p><b>What is a software issue?</b> Software issues are problems that affect the programs and applications that run on a computer, such as the operating system, the drivers, the antivirus, the browser, the office suite, the games, and so on.</p>
